1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3
{ In this chapter, we will examine the unusual and somewhat suspect } 3... Nc6
4. Nf3
{ We will examine two different responses to 4.Nf3.  We'll start with the very rare  4...dxe4, which has only been essayed a few times OTB  (> 426 online games)   and then tackle the more common  4...Nb4, which has been played about a dozen times OTB  (> 200 online games)  . }
