1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3 Nf6
{ which is a typical response to both the Classical variation with 3.Nc3 and the Tarrasch with 3.Nd2. However, as we'll see, it's not very good versus 3.Bd3.   This is reflected in the statistical occurrence of this move, which has featured in less than 60 games OTB.   Surprisingly, it is the 2nd most common move in online games and has been played over 30k times. }
