12... Be7 13. Nb5 { Threatening Nc7+ with a royal fork. } 13... Qb6
{ 13...Bd8  prevents Nc7+ but surrenders control of the a3-f8 diagonal, which White can immediately exploit with  14.Ba3  White is already winning with the huge threat of Nd6+. }
14. Rb1 { Nd6+ picking up the queen is White's threat. } 14... O-O
{ 14...Qd8  leads to similar play as the main line  15.Nf4  O-O  16.O-O  +− White has a winning attack with Qg4/h5 and Re1-e3-g3. }
