{ The alternative retreating move  11...Na7  drops a pawn to  12.Bd2  Black has no good way of defending the pawn on a5. For example  12...Bd8  13.O-O+−  with the idea f4-f5. All of Black's pieces are on the last two ranks of the board so it's no surprise White is already winning. }
12. Qc2
{ This strong move prevents Black from castling since the h7 pawn would drop with check. White is basically already winning. Just take a look at Black's pieces! They are all on the last 3 ranks of the board and hardly have any prospects  (the bishop on c8 is dead so Black is basically playing down a piece)  . The plan is to complete development with Nbc3 and O-O. White should eliminate Black's only good minor piece with a4 and Ba3 and then attack on the kingside with f4-f5.  Based on beta tester feedback and since Chessable has a wide audience, I've decided to mark the following variation that illustrates how play is likely to continue as an alternative. Ambitious and/or higher-rated players can choose to train this alternative variation if they see fit. }
