1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3
{ In this chapter, we'll examine the second most popular response to 3.Bd3 }
3... c5
{ When faced with 3.Bd3, Black plays 3...c5 in just short of 25% of OTB games  (> 500 OTB games)  . It is the third most popular move in internet chess, with over 22k games played. }
4. exd5
{ We'll first tackle the following two dubious captures  4...Qxd5, which has been played more than 50 times OTB  (>2k online games)   and  4...cxd4, which has been essayed a few times OTB  (>700 online games)   before turning our attention to the only serious response  4...exd5, which is much more popular and has been played over 300 times OTB  (>7k online games)  . }
