{ Blocking the check and preparing Bf4, renewing the threat of Nc7+ } 7... Na6
{ This is the only way of preventing Nc7+. } 8. Bf4 Qf6 9. O-O
{ White will follow up with Qd2 and Ng3-e4-d6  (playing Nd6 immediately is also strong but by getting the Ne2 to d6, we ensure we'll keep a knight on this strong outpost)  . Black is way behind in development and will find it very hard to develop his kingside.  Based on beta tester feedback and because Chessable has a wide audience, I've decided to mark the following variation that illustrates how play is likely to continue as an alternative. Ambitious and/or higher-rated players can choose to train this alternative variation if they see fit. }
