{ GM Vladimir Onischuk, a 2600+ 3. Bd3 specialist, won a nice game in 2017 with 6. Bf4 but I prefer the text. You can find this game in the Model games chapter. }
6... Nc6 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O
{ In this concrete position, we castle kingside due to the particular position of black's bishop on c5. We intend to follow up with a3+b4, gaining space on the queenside with tempi. }
8... Nf6 9. a3 O-O
{ The natural   9...a5  to stop b4 is a strategical mistake. The b5 square is now permanently weak and a great outpost for the c3 knight  (which in conjunction with Bf4 would threaten knight jumps to c7 and d6)  . }
10. b4 Be7 11. Bb2
{ The knight on c6 is totally misplaced. In these structures, the knight should be on d7. White is clearly better and will follow up with Qe2, Rad1, and Rfe1. }
