[White "5. 3...dxe4 Part I"]
[Black "Chapter overview"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3 { We have now reached the main Black reply } 3... dxe4
{ which has been played well over 500 times OTB  (>43k online games)  . Statistically, Black plays 3...dxe4 in about 50% of OTB games. }
4. Bxe4 Nf6
{ 4...c5  has no independent value.  5.Ne2  Nf6  6.Bf3  transposes to the coverage in this chapter. }
5. Bf3
{ In this chapter we will be covering the following 5th move alternatives to the main move 5...c5  5...Nc6 is quite rare with only 50+ games OTB  (>3k online games)   5...Nbd7, which has been played more than 50 times OTB  (>3k online games)   5...Bd6, essayed more than 25 times OTB  (>5k online games)   and then we'll look at the following alternatives to the most common move 6...Nc6  6...e5, which was only played a handful of times  (>100 online games)   6...Be7, played over 40 times  (>700 online games)   6...cxd4, played over 15 times  (>1.8k online games)   Finally, we'll examine the following options on move 7  7...e5, played over 55 times  (>700 online games)   7...Nd5, played over 50 times  (>500 online games)   7...Qb6, which only featured in a few games OTB  (>800 online games) }
