6... Nc6 7. Be3 { White develops the bishop and protects the pawn on d4. } 7...
Nd5
{ Several sources claim this move is a mistake. However, after thoroughly analyzing the ensuing lines, I found that Black can reach a dynamically equal position with precise play  (he needs to know 20 moves of theory though!)  . }
