{ Black is trying to exploit the consequences of White's last move, i.e. that after Be3 the b2 pawn is unprotected. }
8. Nbc3 Qxb2 { Capturing the pawn is a mistake. } 9. Rb1 Qa3 10. O-O Qa5 11.
dxc5
{ Regaining the pawn. Material is now equal but Black has lost a lot of time with Qxb2-a3-a5 and, in the meantime, White has developed all of his pieces. }
11... Be7 12. Nd4 { Threatening Nxc6 followed by Bxc6+. } 12... O-O 13. Qe1
{ Threatening Nxc6 and if Black moves the c6 knight away, the b7 pawn will drop. White has a clear edge. }
