Nbc3 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Ne5
{ 9...Nxd4  10.Qxd4  Recapturing with the queen is much stronger than Bxd4. The resulting endgame after the queen exchange is very unpleasant for Black. }
10. O-O Nxf3+ 11. Qxf3
{ White has a huge advantage in development. Here is a sample continuation that ends with a nice tactic: }
11... Be7 12. Rfd1 O-O 13. Nf5
{ With a double-attack on the Qb6 and the Be7. White will emerge with an extra piece:   13...Bc5  14.Ne7+  Note that the bishop on c5 is pinned to the queen on b6.  Kh8  15.Na4  +- Picks up the c5 bishop with a decisive advantage.   13...Qc7  also fails to defend the Be7.  14.Nb5  Qc4  16.Nxe7  White captures the bishop with check so Black has no time to take the knight on c4.  16...Kh8  17.Nd6  +- White has an extra piece. }
