Nxd4 Ne5 9. Nc3
{ In this chapter, we are going to cover of all Black's alternatives on move 9, that is 9... Be7, 9... Bb4 and 9... Nxf3. The main line, 9... a6, is covered in the next chapter. }
9... Be7 10. Qe2 Nxf3+ 11. Qxf3 O-O 12. O-O-O
{ White has completed his development and will play g4 next. The kings are castled on opposite sides so White should start an attack against Black's king. }
12... Bd7 13. g4
{ 13.Qxb7  This is a mistake. Even though White wins a pawn, he opens the b-file for Black to attack White's king.  13...Rb8  ⩱ White's king will come under a serious attack. }
