22... Bc6
{ Attacking the knight on a4 is natural.   22...Bd5  Trying to block the d-file can be met with  23.c4!  bxc3  24.Nxc3  Qc6  25.Nxd5  Qxd5  26.Qe2  With the idea Rd1.  26...Qc5  27.Qd2  f4  Black now wants Qf5+ so White should play  28.Ka1  Now Rd1 and Qd8 checkmate is a big threat. Black must force a repetition with  28...Qd5  29.Qe2  Qc5  30.Qd2= }
