[White "8. Model games"]
[Black " 1-0 Vachier Lagrave,M (2793) -Van der Lende,I (2332) 2018"]
[Result "*"]

{ We are now going to look at a rapid game between GM Maxime Vachier Lagrave and IM Ilias Van Der Lende played in the 2018 PRO League group stage. }
1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Bd3 dxe4 4. Bxe4 Nf6 5. Bf3 c5 6. Ne2 Nc6 7. Be3 Nd5 8.
Bxd5 Qxd5 9. Nbc3 Qh5 10. Nb5
{ This was all covered inchapter 5 of the course. } 10... Rb8
{ This move is a blunder.  As mentioned in the course, Black should play   10...cxd4  when White can get a slightly better position after Nc7+ and Bf4. }
11. O-O
{ White missed the opportunity to immediately strike with   11.d5  !  11...exd5  12.Nc7  Kd8  13.Nxd5  +- White is threatening Nf6+ and Bf4 is also coming. With his king stuck in the middle of the board, Black's position is hopeless. }
11... Be7
{ A better try would have been   11...a6  12.Nc7  Kd8  13.Bf4  e5  White is still clearly for choice after  14.dxe5  !± but the game goes on. }
12. d5 { MVL does not miss the opportunity to play d5 twice. } 12... exd5 13.
Bf4 { Hitting the rook on b8, which has nowhere to run to. } 13... O-O
{ 13...Ra8  would have lost the rook to the following fork  14.Nc7  +- } 14.
Bxb8 Nxb8 15. Nf4 Qxd1 16. Raxd1
{ White is up an exchange for only a pawn and had no trouble bringing the point home. }
16... d4 17. Rfe1
{ Picking up a pawn with   17.Nxa7  was also winning. MVL prefers to bring the f1 rook into the game with a tempo against black's bishop on e7. }
17... Bd8 18. Nd6 { Hitting the c8 bishop. } 18... Bg4 19. f3 Bc7 20. Nxb7 Bxf3
{ Black tries to grab a pawn taking advantage of the fact that the knight on f4 is hanging. White isn't too bothered though, as the c5 pawn is also en prise. }
21. gxf3 Bxf4 22. Nxc5 Be3+ 23. Kg2
{ White will now turn his attention to the d4 pawn. } 23... Rc8 24. c3 Nc6
{ 24...Rxc5  is met by  25.Rxe3  +- Note that the Black cannot capture the rook with dxe3, as that would allow a back rank checmate with Rd1-d8. }
25. Nb3 { The d4 pawn is about to drop. } 25... f5 26. Nxd4 Nxd4 27. Rxe3
{ Black resigned since he is an exchange down and the d1 rook is about to get to the 7th rank.   1-0  (27)  Vachier Lagrave, M  (2793)  -Van der Lende, I  (2332)  chess.com INT 2018 }
