[Round "?"]
[White "9. Puzzles"]
[Black "Exercise #8"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r2qr1k1/4bppb/5n1p/p1NpN3/1n1P1QBB/1P6/5PPP/2R2RK1 w - - 0 1"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ This position arose from the3. Bd3 c5 variation. White has a lot of pieces around Black's king but Black seems to have everything covered. What did White play in this position ? }
1. Nxf7 Kxf7 2. Be6+ Kf8 3. Nd7+
{ Black has to give up the queen since the knight on f6 is pinned. } 3... Qxd7
4. Bxd7
{ White easily converted his material advantage in 1-0 Westerberg, Jonathan  (2500)  - Schneider, Stefan  (2390)  2018. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "9. Puzzles"]
[Black "Exercise #9"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "r1bqk2r/pp3ppp/4pn2/1N2n3/1b6/2N1BB2/PPP2PPP/R2QK2R b KQkq - 0 10"]
[SetUp "1"]

10... O-O
{ Black has just played the natural O-O. However, this is actually a mistake. Can you spot how White can win material? }
11. Qxd8 Rxd8 12. Nc7 Rb8 13. Bxa7
{ Wins a pawn and the exchange as the Rb8 has nowhere to go.    (this was all mentioned in the9...Bb4 #3 variation.)  . }
