{ White centralized the queen with } 18. Qe4
{ with the deadly threat of Ra4, trapping Black's queen on a2! Thus } 18... Bd7
{ White was threatening Ra4 to trap Black's queen. As such, Black decided to prevent this with ...Bd7. However, it does not save Black. How can White crash through Black's position? }
19. Rxd7 { A beautiful shot that wins the game on the spot. } 19... Kxd7 20.
Qxb7+ Kd6 { 20...Ke8  drops both rooks with check  21.Qxa8+  Ke7  22.Qxh8+− }
21. Rd1+ Ke5
{ Black's king is now in the middle of the board. Onto to the next puzzle to see how White can finish Black off. }
