{ As mentioned in the previous puzzle, White managed to drag Black's king all the way to the center of the board. White has three pieces against Black's lone king. How should White finish Black off? }
1. Qe7 { Stopping Black from retreating with ...Kf6. } 1... Rhe8
{ Black can't run away with   1...Kf4  as  2.Qf6  is checkmate. } 2. Rd5+
{ A stunning sacrifice! } 2... Kxd5 3. Qc5#
{ A beautiful finish to the game. @@StartBracket@@this was actually mentioned in a clickable variation in the9...a6 #4 variation. }
