[SetUp "1"]

{ This position arose from the 3...Nf6 variation. } 17. Qh6
{ White is threatening Nh5 and Qg7 checkmate. Note that Black will not be able to capture the knight on h5 due to Qxh7 checkmate. }
17... f5
{ Trying to cut off the Bc2 from the attack. How can White crash through Black's kingside? }
18. Nxg6 { Breaking down Black's king shelter. } 18... hxg6 19. Qxg6+ Kh8 20.
h4
{ The ROVER @@StartBracket@@rook up and over!@@EndBracket@@ is inbound and Black's king will be mated shortly thereafter! For example: }
20... Qd8 21. Rh3 { With the idea Qh6+ and Rg3-g7 checkmate. } 21... Qe8 22.
Qh6+ Kg8 23. Rg3+ Kf7 24. Rg7# *

